abstract: Proctor & Gamble’s big 2014 Winter Olympics ad glorifies the sacrifices moms and children make in the name of athletic glory (once again, dads aren’t in the picture). I say Thanks, Mom and Dad, for letting me enjoy the sport without the sacrifice.
snippet: Proctor & Gamble’s big 2014 Winter Olympics ad glorifies the sacrifices moms and children make in the name of athletic glory (once again, dads aren’t in the picture). I say Thanks, Mom and Dad, for letting me enjoy the sport without the sacrifice.
lead_paragraph: Has Procter & Gamble’s “Pick Them Back Up campaign brought a tear to your eye yet? It’s a powerful combination of exhilarating sports imagery, dramatic music and tender moments between mothers and kids. Moms encourage their kids to get back up after various athletic setbacks, from faceplanting on the ice rink as tots to recovering from injuries as teens, then finally sharing the sweet taste of victory with their adult daughters and sons.

abstract: In many states under single-party control, lawmakers are steering away from the divisive battles on abortion, gun control, collective bargaining and large tax cuts that have marked recent sessions in state capitols.
snippet: In many states under single-party control, lawmakers are steering away from the divisive battles on abortion, gun control, collective bargaining and large tax cuts that have marked recent sessions in state capitols.
lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — One year ago, Gov. John W. Hickenlooper, a Colorado Democrat, stood before a state legislature controlled by his party and laid out an aggressive agenda that included a sweeping expansion of gun-control laws after the mass shooting at an Aurora movie house. “Why not have universal background checks for all gun sales?” he asked.

abstract: FirstEnergy promised to report on what it could do to cut emissions after prodding by shareholders like New York State and Connecticut pension funds.
snippet: FirstEnergy promised to report on what it could do to cut emissions after prodding by shareholders like New York State and Connecticut pension funds.
lead_paragraph: FirstEnergy, one of the country’s largest electric companies, has agreed to work toward reducing its carbon emissions in response to pressure from shareholders including New York State and Connecticut pension funds, New York Comptroller Thomas P. DiNapoli said on Tuesday.

abstract: “Generation War,” a film about early-1940s Germany, is notable for what it includes and for what it leaves out.
snippet: “Generation War,” a film about early-1940s Germany, is notable for what it includes and for what it leaves out.
lead_paragraph: “Generation War,” which was broadcast as a mini-series on German television last year, is perhaps more interesting as an artifact of the present than as a representation of the past. As the Second World War slips from living memory, as Germany asserts its dominant role in Europe with increasing confidence, and as long-suppressed information emerges from the archives of former Eastern bloc countries, the war’s cultural significance for Germans has shifted.

abstract: The mayor of Richmond, Calif., is pushing a novel use of eminent domain to prevent foreclosures. Financial firms are very, very unhappy.
snippet: The mayor of Richmond, Calif., is pushing a novel use of eminent domain to prevent foreclosures. Financial firms are very, very unhappy.
lead_paragraph: You can’t fight city hall, the saying goes. But Gayle McLaughlin, the mayor of Richmond, Calif., a city of 100,000 souls, would tell you that fighting Wall Street is harder. Even for city hall.

abstract: Alumni of ThinkFilm have become a force in an industry that has been learning to think smaller, make do with less and live more by wit than a fat bankroll.
snippet: Alumni of ThinkFilm have become a force in an industry that has been learning to think smaller, make do with less and live more by wit than a fat bankroll.
lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — In two weeks, the feisty operatives of an ever tighter, tougher independent film business will gather at the annual Sundance Film Festival.

abstract: A frosty family trip in pursuit of the aurora borealis slides between watching and waiting, panic and prayer.
snippet: A frosty family trip in pursuit of the aurora borealis slides between watching and waiting, panic and prayer.
lead_paragraph: We hurtled across the tundra in the dark. The old train chugged, rattled, occasionally whined. As the sun came up around 10 a.m., the world faded from black to cobalt to white and every shade between. All was snow; it was just a matter of how much, where, what shape. Black spruce trees draped in white rose up from the ground like crystals of hoarfrost.

abstract: America's obsession with football crosses social and political divides and makes a hefty profit, but players' bodies are paying the price.
snippet: America's obsession with football crosses social and political divides and makes a hefty profit, but players' bodies are paying the price.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The United States, polarized politically and splintered socially, is about to experience one of its few widely shared moments: the professional football playoffs.

abstract: A former Marine on death row for shooting his girlfriend and her brother has filed an appeal, arguing that the jury at his trial was not fully informed about his post-traumatic stress disorder.
snippet: A former Marine on death row for shooting his girlfriend and her brother has filed an appeal, arguing that the jury at his trial was not fully informed about his post-traumatic stress disorder.
lead_paragraph: The car would not stop. Flares did not stop it. Shots fired into the engine had no effect. As far as the four Marines stationed at a roadside checkpoint in Iraq knew, the sedan hurtling toward them was a bomb on wheels.
